  "texts": [
    "We visualize all three metrics and observe that: • As the window size 𝑊 increases, the performance of the trajectory length and the cumulative reward metrics decrease for all methods.",
    "This implies that when users are more susceptible to the influence of filter bubbles, the model faces greater challenges in learning to improve users' long-term engagement.",
    "• BiLLP outperforms all baselines in terms of both the trajectory length and the cumulative reward metrics, which demonstrates the robustness of BiLLP in different environments.",
    "• BiLLP obtains a relatively higher score in terms of the singleround in different environments, which indicates it successfully captures user interests while avoiding excessive emphasis on immediate responses.",
    "Results with DifferentBase Models."
